## Translation File Config

Locale files are exposed to CloudCannon via `data_config` in `cloudcannon.config.yml`:

```yaml
data_config:
  locales_fr:
    path: rosey/locales/fr.json
  locales_de:
    path: rosey/locales/de.json
```

## Build-Time CLI

`rosey-cloudcannon-connector write-locales` reads Rosey's `base.json` and creates/updates locale JSON files, adding new keys while preserving existing translations. With `--dest <dir>`, it also writes a locale manifest to `{dest}/_rcc/locales.json` that the injector fetches at runtime for locale discovery.

## Agent Skills

The `skills/` directory contains structured markdown instructions for AI coding agents. Users add them to their project via:

```bash
npx rosey-cloudcannon-connector add-skills [--dest .cursor/skills]
```

| Skill | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `translate-locale-files` | Translate untranslated and stale entries in locale files. Includes `scripts/prepare-translation.mjs` (classify, dedup, extract task file) and `scripts/merge-translation.mjs` (merge, validate HTML, clean up) |
| `translate-content-collections` | Translate split-by-directory content collection files. Includes `scripts/prepare-content-translation.mjs` (diff source vs locale, extract translatable fields) and `scripts/merge-content-translation.mjs` (patch translations back into MDX/MD) |
| `make-site-multilingual` | Set up Rosey/RCC/CloudCannon from scratch (with SSG-specific supplements) |
| `migrate-i18n-to-rosey` | Replace an existing i18n system with Rosey |
| `migrate-rcc-v1-to-v2` | Upgrade from RCC v1 to v2 |
